Figure 1 shows the overall structure of our minimal PBPK model, which was implemented in MATLAB R2020b (The MathWorks, Natick, MA, US). The model adopts the general minimal PBPK approach proposed by Cao and Jusko [26] and describes two lumped compartments for interstitial fluid (ISF) and intracellular fluid (ICF). The plasma circulation of the drug is described by dividing plasma into the renal circulatory system (RCS), the hepatic circulatory system (HCS), and the remaining part of the global circulatory system (CS). Each compartment is assumed homogeneous [27] so that in the generic compartment \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
