Structure of the minimal PBPK model. The rectangles represent the compartments of the model: three plasma compartments (dark orange), the lumped ISF compartment (mustard), and the lumped ICF compartment (cyan). The arrows describe the drug flows, i.e. administration, exchange between compartments, metabolism, and excretion (colour figure online)

