Patients received from 1 to 17 administrations of the drug, over a time period from 36 h to 352 d, for a grand total of 396 infusions. The dataset reports the amount of each administration (1–9 g, or 0.62–5.16 g/m2), the time of administration, and the infusion duration (0.32–7.71 h). We assume that the administered infusion rate was constant over the reported duration. Following administration, Mei et al. [41] measured plasma MTX concentrations every day, until the concentration fell below 0.05 µM, yielding 657 measurements (\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
